SIMPLE: martyrdom
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Martyrdom
<hw>Mar"tyr*dom</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Martyr</ets>
+ <ets>-dom</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition of a martyr;
the death of a martyr; the suffering of death on account of adherence to
the Christian faith, or to any cause.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I came from <qex>martyrdom</qex> unto this peace.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Affliction; torment; torture.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Martyrization</ent>⟦br⟧
